MQTT Qos
In MQTT, Quality of Service (QoS) defines the guarantee level for message delivery between publisher and subscriber, balancing reliability
and overhead with three levels: QoS 0 (At Most Once) for "fire and forget," 
QoS 1 (At Least Once) for guaranteed delivery (potentially with duplicates), 
and QoS 2 (Exactly Once) for the highest assurance, ensuring each message is received once and only once

